</div>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><a name="Circular_fisheye" id="Circular_fisheye"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Angle_of_view&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Circular fisheye">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Circular fisheye</span></h3>
<p>A <a href="/wiki/Fisheye_lens#Circular" title="Fisheye lens">circular fisheye lens</a> (as opposed to a full-frame fisheye) is an example of a lens where the angle of coverage is less than the angle of view. The image projected onto the film is circular because the diameter of the image projected is <i>narrower</i> than that needed to cover the widest portion of the film.</p>
<p><a name="Common_lens_angles_of_view" id="Common_lens_angles_of_view"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Angle_of_view&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: Common lens angles of view">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Common lens angles of view</span></h2>
